				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">As was said, cc65 can handle banking with some help from the user. I haven't used cc65 for C, only assembly, but I have macro code to enhance the .segment command and other macros that create a 'bank' property for all function's entry points. With MMC3 it seems ideal to setup the 8k banks at $8000 and $E000 as fixed banks, and the rest banked at $A000 and $C000. I can designate the banks as code or data. Code banks are tracked and calls verfied that they are banking/not banking as needed at build. This works as long as you follow the rule to not bank code banks in NMI, otherwise you need a currentCodeBank variable. Databanks are tracked with a variable and banked as needed, but each label is also assigned a bank property. This could be enhanced by tracking and verifying databanks at runtime with Lua. (Lua: see NintendulatorDX).</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

